text: Had egg & onion prata (taste like murtabak without the meat), a plain (kosong) prata and a cup of coffee at 9pm+. Prata not bad. You can see this place when u pass by the main road. There is a side gate for u to enter. Can park on the side of the road.

If you‚Äôre at summer camp, you can buy snacks at the canteen. This kind of canteen is a little shop. At the canteen, you can buy little things like potato chips or a can opener. A canteen is like a convenience store. The other kind of canteen is good if you‚Äôre going on a hike ‚Äî fill it up with water and put it in your backpack, since there probably aren‚Äôt any of those other kinds of canteens out in the woods.
Ate here several times while on a business visit to Singapore. The food is great and the portions they give are quite large. Service is quick and prices are great too.
